  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6555.28 sitting below the massive +20.7B gamma wall at 6580, dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as they're short delta and need to purchase futures on any weakness - this is creating a strong floor around current levels with the -16B negative gamma at 6550 providing additional buying pressure. The PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively fade any rally attempt toward 6580 where they'll dump futures into strength, creating a tight trading range between 6550-6580 with mean reversion bias. \n\nWatch for violent dealer buying if we test 6550 (amplifying negative gamma) and expect heavy selling pressure on any push toward the 6580 max positive gamma wall - the 111% GEX surge indicates this setup just became extremely rigid.",
